          "INC-SOURCE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "9Be(18O,13B). A secondary beam of 13B at 23",
                " MeV/nucleon was produced from a primary beam of 18O",
                " at 60 MeV/nucleon bombarding on a 3.8-mm-thick 9Be",
                " target. The beam intensity and purity of 13B were",
                " approximately equal to 2.0E4 particles per second and",
                " 98%, respectively."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "A(CD2)n target with a thickness of 3.98 mg/cm2 is",
                " made from deuterated polyethylene."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "SCIN"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Two plastic scintillation detectors provide",
                " both the time-of-flight and the energy losses of the",
                " fragments, were used to discriminate the secondary",
                " beam."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "PPAC"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " The incident angles and hit positions on the",
                " targets of the 13B beam were determined by two",
                " position-sensitive parallel plate avalanche chambers",
                " with resolutions less than 0.3 deg and 1.5 mm."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "TELES",
                "SISD",
                "SI",
                "CSICR"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Four sets of charged particle",
                " telescopes named T0, T1, T2, and TA were installed in",
                " a large scattering chamber to detect the",
                " projectilelike particles around the beam direction,",
                " the targetlike charged particles, the deuterons",
                " elastically scattered from 13B, and the protons from",
                " the 2H(13B, p)14B reaction, respectively. T0, T1,",
                " and T2 were all composed of a double-sided silicon",
                " strip detector, one or two large surface silicon",
                " detectors, and a layer of 4-cm-thick CsI(Tl)",
                " crystals. TA, a set of the annular double-sided",
                " silicon strip detector composed of six sectors."
              ]
            }
          ],
